[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating Tomcat configuration**\n\nAlright, I've got a potential issue here. If there’s no web.xml, it seems the StandardContext defaults to using defaultweb.xml from the conf directory. For embedded Tomcat, it might look in catalinaBase/conf/web.xml and log if it's missing, but it should still start up.\n\nAlso, the existing TomcatTests utilize Tomcat.addDefaultMimeTypeMappings. I’m considering whether the raw HostConfig context attempts to parse DefaultWebXml, which could lead to failure if there's no conf/web.xml. I need to gather more information on this.\n\n**Considering webapp configuration issues**\n\nIt seems a cat can start empty web apps without configuration, but I need to check if there's an issue without WebResourceRoot. If everything’s okay, it'll process the context web XML and use the default. However, I see potential problems, such as the docBase directory possibly lacking WEB-INF/classes and web.xml. Also, there might be an issue if `tomcat.stop()` is affected by contexts failing after an assertion. I should clarify that I didn’t run tests per instructions since that’s handled externally.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_078636dd73a4a1d1016a35355eb1448195ace759352900020a\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqNTVtPwXaOxaJ5URIiyTOWE70l7g9It9k8Btjcnfjvo5elinMTyJ03OMAUNjCFw6fxzU28FEjGmlSPxA8okSfJRhIHaqdXKarpIwVvS7Jaey8IpfZ_fUPsHNDJ8wUFVzVl_g-yj7zKoLIAreRaxyexEg47Gftgx-I0UIFiU3JGb14SOwHeVNE0Jvh2jJ_Aoe6hREZUbKQFIrxyl9E8R2AhznT4eJTQWag1TnHkR4PoNFd5GhM58BaLxrf9Rm0Nz4fx-yU9etd7Q60prBfrzNCgtOMUNruXXBH3eZEGTOdqEKhMRDgbuzXkBBmuQhE3lG95QLPk3k-6hDijoQF_wYhTb3kBL7x3wEHsQTxvX3SMfHAVX8hVMomdtCtf04I8rX5FXwnAcnJ8QbuIg4gSYXdn98enBGfMH9JNMxl9GekkkxjbcVxiVsvNUSCSVGeNXSKZ8R3cmDlr3Zb94YLc3hpNaKxn2laR5sSO-_miQ4KpsTvdkDjCYVk-2dWa05ZeNW9uYO6pGctuTqnEzJG5wLx5JbVknCE9uPWY6zORlQtiunklyltca69vGHwCXDOsqAdvL09eFsQ5FkQ4ap-OARJj9mXkoQsR